e Sanskrit classics are presented and applied differently in the college and gurukula, producing a variety of relationships with these texts among practitioners. By interrogating the politics surrounding the place of the Sanskrit classics in ayurvedic curricula, this book reveals a spectrum of views about the history and tradition of Ayurveda in modern India.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMedicine, AyurvedicxStudy and teachingzIndiazKerala. 0aMedicine, AyurvediczIndiazKeralaxHistory. 0aReligion. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520383555?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520383555zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520383555/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-UCY